  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Currently we rely on `Version` in CRI to check whether the container runtime is up. This single binary state may not be indicative of whether the runtime is ready, nor provide enough information about subcomponents in the runtime. For example, the default network plugin kubenet reports an error on the [`Status`](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/e2c96db72b6ef5819b08f976861a344ea9430373/pkg/kubelet/network/kubenet/kubenet_linux.go#L534-L544) call if the CNI plugin binaries are missing or pod CIDR is not ready. Even if network is not ready, kubelet can still run host network pods (#35526).\n\nOne option to report the network readiness is to reuse the `Version` call and add network plugin version and names, if the version of that is missing, kubelet will report node \"NotReady\" and stop syncing non-hostnetwork pods. However, this overloads the `Version` call, and is not as flexible as just adding a `Status` call. Thoughts?\n\n/cc @kubernetes/sig-node @euank @yifan-gu @mrunalp @feiskyer @bprashanth @thockin \n",
